CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 7, reads: "Attention State Liquor Control Board - How Many More Taverns Can Homewood-Brushton Stand? Five of Brushton's Six - Among the six liquor dispensing establishments in six blocks of Brushton are (left photo, left to right): The Brushton Grill, Breil's Cafe, Ben's Restaurant and The Colonial Inn, all at the intersection of Kelly St. and Brushton Ave.... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: 600 block of Brushton Avenue with Ruth Ann Shoppe, Lowe Brothers Paints, Weber's Hardware, Brushton Grill, Colonial Inn, and Sam De Maria, near intersection of Kelly Street, Homewood
